
what?
• Data Attributes are a special kind of attribute the word prefix starts with "data". 
• So these data attributes are always stored in the DataSet Object.
Where?
• we use data attributes quite a lot when we work with UI, especially when we need to store data in the user Interface,
so basically in the HTML
why?
• Data attributes are useful for storing information that may be needed by JavaScript but don't have a natural place in HTML attributes.
• They provide a way to associate custom data with HTML elements for scripting purposes.


HTML:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Document</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1 class="juvva" data-custom-info="Edi costume attributr anta">
      Hello, javascript
    </h1>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
JavaScript:

const HeaderEle = document.querySelector(".juvva");

const displayInfo = Info.dataset.customInfo;
console.log(displayInfo);

O/P:Edi costume attributr anta

